@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### Categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories

### List transactions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/transactions?isExpense=true

### Create transaction (auto-categorize if category omitted)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2025-01-20",
  "description": "FreshMart Supermarket",
  "amount": 32.50,
  "isExpense": true
}

### Categorize via API (proxies to Python service)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/categorization
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "RideShare Trip",
  "isExpense": true
}

### Analytics — monthly spend by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/spending-by-category

### Analytics — average monthly per category
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/average-monthly-by-category

### Analytics — top merchants
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/top-merchants?limit=10

### Dashboard — months & filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/months
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/expense-categories

### Dashboard — Grafana-equivalent panels
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/spend-by-category?month=2023-01
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/budget-502030/actual?month=2023-01
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/budget-502030/target?month=2023-01
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/daily-expenditures
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/earnings-vs-expenditures
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/category-pivot?metric=amount
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/monthly-by-categories?categories=Food,Groceries,Transport

### Upload CSV (multipart — use IDE or curl)
# curl -F "file=@seed/transactions.demo.csv" "{{baseUrl}}/api/import/csv?autoCategorize=true"
